author: The Associated Press
title: TOP 10 iBOOKS
text: Posted Oct. 11, 2015 at 7:48 AM By The Associated Press Posted Oct. 11, 2015 at 7:48 AM Holland, Mich. Top paid iBooks for week ending Oct. 5, 2015: 1. The Martian by Andy Weir (Crown/Archetype) 2. The Murder House by David Ellis & James Patterson (Little, Brown and Company) 3. Make Me by Lee Child (Random House Publishing Group) 4. The Girl in the Spider's Web by David Lagercrantz (Knopf Doubleday Publishing Group) 5. Killing Reagan by Bill O'Reilly & Martin Dugard (Henry Holt and Co.) 6. Pretty Girls by Karin Slaughter (William Morrow) 7. After You by Jojo Moyes (Penguin Publishing Group) 8. The Girl on the Train by Paula Hawkins (Penguin Publishing Group) 9. The Memory Thief by Emily Colin (Random House Publishing Group) 10. Why Not Me? by Mindy Kaling (Crown/Archetype) By The Associated Press
